@baseUrl = http://localhost:4004
@email = admin@test.com
@password = admin123

### 1. Health check (no auth needed)
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 2. Login — copy the accessToken from response into @token below
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 3. Set your token here after login
@token = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJ1c2VySWQiOiJ1c2VyLTEiLCJyb2xlIjoiYWRtaW4iLCJpYXQiOjE3ODA5NDIxNzMsImV4cCI6MTc4MDk0NTc3M30.YEpkRrRT2NrEZgZPEILnchnDvSsbirJkkvwcDmmiTvE

### 4. Hit protected route with valid token
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Hit protected route with no token — expect 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/profile

### 6. Hit protected route with garbage token — expect 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/profile
Authorization: Bearer thisisnotavalidtoken

### 7. Hit unknown route — expect 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/unknown/route

### 8. Hit public route (no auth) — expect proxy attempt
GET {{baseUrl}}/public/something